Abstract:

This guide is for those who have problem in E3 Hard mode Last dance or for reference in clearing E3 Last Dance in general without using the 7 historical ships for braching rule require in B-C-G-H-J. This guide will introduce the background and the journal into this B-C-D-G-H-J with CTF set up as well as recommandation for further improvement and conclusion.

Introduction

As noted by everyone in the comment section, E3 is the jumping gab of difficulty of everyday Kancolle event were E1 and E2 Hard can be consider as a walk in the park but E3 is Hellist in so many ways, although not as hellist as previous event as this map is the last map with lock mechanism while everyone could manage to give in everything they had but not with their best potential ships yet. Various challenger had run insane or just despair with resource shortages because of fail attemps. Hence, from the frontier recomendation of using 7 historical ships had been seem to be the best only hope of light to clear E3 for everyone.

Background

Resource after E2 Hard: ~140k fuel, ~65k ammo, ~110 steel, ~80k bauxite, ~2.5k bucket (Thanks to daily 10 251 250 10)

Fleet strength: HQ lvl 110, 70+ ships are level 90 and above, ~15 ships level 90~80 (Money lover, 95/100)

Experience: Start since spring 2014 event, play casually because of lack of time

Goal: Aim for the reward except Medal with least effort

15 August (Monday)[[File:E3H_H_node_S_rank_2.png|thumb|400px|E3H H node S rank]]

Clear H2 Hard and start H3 Hard

Because of lack of slot and lack of 1 more historical ship: Kongou (98), Haruna (98), Choukai (97), Fubuki (89), Mikuma (84), Mogami (82), I gave up on using the braching rule and look for alternative road such as B-C-D-G-H-J. During that time, frontier had assumed that (BB+CV)>4? result in D > F which would bring you down to a maelstorm node which reduced fuels further after going through an [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Events/Mechanics airstrike node (-8% fuel and -4% ammo)][1], after that, had to face punishment of Wo at G and Duo Summer BB Hime in H, result in discouragement of the use of Heavy ships in this map. The information were so little, hence the fleet composite set up recommended by frontier during that time was something like 1BB 3CA 2CV + 1CL 3DD 1 CA 1 FBB, with so many CA, one would get Taihaed easily by Wo and DuoBBs as well as in Boss node, hence less player here would actually took on this composite and cleared it. But during that time I found the excelsheet with ships used for braching don't match up as mention, some with 4 (BB+CV) still directed to maelstorm while some already 6 (BB+CV) still going D to G. Curious with this result, I decided to make more runs beside scripping the boss hp while wasting resources to find out more about its braching rule.

16 August (Tuesday)[[File:E3_roading_2.png|thumb|400px|E3 roading]]

Unexpected E3 Hard clear

In the beginning, I start up with fleet composite mentioned on the article and increased the fleet strength little by little in the process of scripping boss hp if the fleet make it through the boss. With only LBAS focus on pre-boss and sent in pre-boss support expedition. During the run, [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/User:Kenji135 Kenji135] share that wikiwiki say Bismarck or 4 CV(B) bring your to F node from D while [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/User:Kurokami11 Kurokami11], the OP [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Talk:Summer_2016_Event/@comment-Kurokami11-20160815200447 varified the claim of Bismarck in braching] [2]. With the available information from frontier in the spreadsheet that prove 4 CV or Bismarck direct to maelstorm, I slowly challenged the limit of the braching rule with my heavy ships but to my suprise, it when into Final Dance much more earlier than I expect. I switched in offencieve ships and gears, start boss support expedition, train all LBAS plane ranks and set 1 LBAS to attack the boss. First try, reached boss with 1 chuuhaed, all support triggered and kill/damage the enemies, only left 2 chuued Boss vs Taiha/Chuuha DD/CL, Green CA/BB after day battle. But in night battle, my FBBs got Taihaed/Chuuhaed before they fired while Choukai barely did any damage to Harbour Hime but manage to bring her down to Taihaed. Finally my last chuuhaed Haruna aim and kill DJ hime result in not clearing. After resting for a while to regain my sanity after got shock by how all my LBAS plane got reck into no rank, I decided to give up in ranking my LBAS plane and go for another round. Second try, 3 chuuhaed ship passed DuoBBHimes, when to boss node, LBAS done crap damage, boss support not trigger, both FBBs got Taihaed. I was very disapointed that time that I did not bother to look. But untill the end of the day battle I looked back, my escort fill with 3 chuuhaed DD/CL/CA and 2 Taihaed FBB vs 2 Green Princess. I was almost going to retried at that point but screw it just keep going until the end. Night battle start, Bang Bang, Ooshio double 200+ damage, follow by Ooyodo coup de grace both sniped the Harbour summer Hime. I was speechless. Then I posted the fleet into [http://kancolle.wikia.com/wiki/Talk:Summer_2016_Event/@comment-Lici_Ui-20160816091754 the comment section] [3], updated the braching rule main article and when to sleep.

